Jenna Etheridge, News24The hammer and toy gun that were taken off a man who hopped over into a Walmer property and was met by a martial arts enthusiast. (Walmer Neighbourhood Watch) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Port Elizabeth - A man who jumped into a yard in Walmer, Port Elizabeth, with a hammer could not have anticipated being met by someone trained in martial arts.Police said the 18-year-old man was tackled after trespassing on Sunday morning.&ldquo;The owner&rsquo;s son spotted the suspect, who lunged at him with a hammer and a firearm. A struggle ensued between the two but the suspect was overpowered by the karate enthusiast,&rdquo; said Colonel Priscilla Naidu.While on the ground, the trespasser produced a firearm but was disarmed and securely subdued until police arrived, the Walmer Neighbourhood watch said on Facebook.Naidu said the firearm turned out to be a toy.The man was arrested on charges of trespassing, pointing of a firearm and being in possession of a housebreaking implement.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.